news.title: Rajasthan: 48,000 incomplete PMAY-G homes in 10 districts to be inspected
news.para: Rural development and panchayati raj minister Ramesh Chand Meena on Friday gave directions to conduct a state-level inspection of 48,344 houses in 10 districts, the construction of which remained incomplete under the Pradhan Mantri Awaas Yojana-Grameen (PMAY-G) during the period 2016-17 to

news.title: Nashik civic body nod to over 5,100 building plans in last fiscal
news.para: Out of the 356 crore, Rs 193 crore was collected in the last four months of the financial year — between December 1 and March 31. An NMC official said the civic body gave approval to 5,174 building plan proposals during the last fiscal year.

news.title: Ludhiana development body razes five illegal colonies
news.para: The five colonies demolished were Nandi, Vashnavi, Khushi in Laddian village, Sarpanch Colony in Churpur and Ashirwaad Colony in South City.

news.title: Maharashtra government stays forcible recovery of non-agricultural tax
news.para: In 2018, the state government lifted the stay and issued fresh guidelines for recovery of NA tax. This tax has been imposed on housing societies across the state except the Mumbai island city.

news.title: Indore: Builder booked for developing an illegal colony
news.para: The builder Rajkumar Parmar, a resident of Sirpur Main Road, had allegedly prepared a fake deed, mentioning his name as a partner with another builder, and later developed plots on private agriculture land and sold them, the police said.

news.title: Stay indoors, switch off ACs: Neighbours prepare for Supertech twin towers' test blast
news.para: The test blast would be carried out to ascertain the exact amount of explosives that would be required to bring down the two towers — Apex and Ceyane — next month.

news.title: Cement demand expected to grow over 7% in 2022, says Ambuja Cements
news.para: The growth would be helped by factors such as infrastructure growth, demand for housing, increase in rural incomes and industrial growth, said Ambuja Cements, part of Swiss building material major Holcim group.

news.title: Maharashtra plans to offer stamp duty sop to spur cluster redevelopment of 56 Mhada layouts
news.para: During a review meeting at the chief minister's official residence Varsha on Friday, CM Uddhav Thackeray directed officials to examine whether developers can be given time till an occupation certificate is issued to pay stamp duty for this redevelopment.

news.title: Canada bans foreign home buyers for two years to cool market
news.para: Finance Minister Chrystia Freeland took a number of measures to tamp down speculation and demand amid record home prices in announcing the federal budget for the year.

news.title: Haryana completes drone flying target in 6,286 Lal Dora villages
news.para: Under SVAMITVA, till date more than 19 lakh property cards have been made. Besides this, the 30 days notice period for raising claims and objections invited under section 26 of Haryana Panchayat Raj Act is also completed by April, 20.

news.title: Will hand over keys of houses to 1 lakh poor people in UP within 100 days: Deputy CM
news.para: The state government will also constitute 50,000 new self-help groups under the State Rural Livelihood Mission to augment women's income in rural areas within the same time period, he told PTI in an interview here.v

news.title: RBI extends rationalised home loan norms till March 2023
news.para: In October 2020, the Reserve Bank as a countercyclical measure to deal with the COVID situation had rationalised the risk weights by linking them only with Loan to Value (LTV) ratios for all new housing loans sanctioned up to March 31, 2022.

news.title: Chandigarh: Unearned profit on property down from 33.33% to 25%
news.para: Unearned profit is defined as the difference between the price paid by the original allottee and the market value of the property at the time of transfer.

news.title: Karnataka likely to continue 10% cut on property guidance value for another three months
news.para: "I had earlier slashed the property guidance value by 10 percent for three months....it was for the benefit of the people, there has been good response to it from across the state. We have been able to generate Rs 1,300 crore more revenue than the set target of Rs 12,000 crore," Ashoka said.

news.title: Gurugram: Illegal colony being built in Bandhwari demolished
news.para: The developer was building a road network, damp-proof courses, boundary walls and some buildings in the area. A team led by MCG assistant engineer Waseem Akram demolished them.
